{"title":"Rocky Mountain Bikes sharpens their Instincts for evolving trail performance","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/03/09/rocky-mountain-bikes-sharpens-their-instincts-for-evolving-trail-performance/","date":1615276909000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>There’s something to be said about one bike that can do it all. Rocky Mountain Bikes is continuing to streamline their models, and the updated Instinct now serves as their most versatile, mid-travel trail bike. With 140/150mm of travel and re-tuned Smoothlink suspension, RMB has revised the Instinct to eat up miles of trail while handling aggressive riding better.</p><p>Many features introduced on RMB’s recently updated Altitudes carry over to the new Instincts: Most notably the frame tubing is similar, smaller frames ride on smaller wheels, and the Instinct gets a +/-10mm chainstay length flip-chip.</p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Bzgpg3j3Irc?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" ezoid=\"0.6467143516194762\"></iframe></span></p><p>With the release of the revised Altitudes, RMB dropped their Instinct BC model and absorbed it into the Altitude lineup. They’ve now done something similar with the Instinct: Rocky Mountain is discontinuing their 27.5” Thunderbolt bikes, relying on the updated Instinct line to serve our mid-travel needs.</p><h2>2021 Rocky Mountain Instinct frame updates:</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134744/RMB-Instinct-2021-complete-studio.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134744/RMB-Instinct-2021-complete-studio.jpg\" alt=\"Rocky Mountain Bikes 2021 Instinct, angle\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134744/RMB-Instinct-2021-complete-studio.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134744/RMB-Instinct-2021-complete-studio.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134744/RMB-Instinct-2021-complete-studio-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134744/RMB-Instinct-2021-complete-studio-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134744/RMB-Instinct-2021-complete-studio-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134744/RMB-Instinct-2021-complete-studio-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134744/RMB-Instinct-2021-complete-studio-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134744/RMB-Instinct-2021-complete-studio.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134744/RMB-Instinct-2021-complete-studio-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134744/RMB-Instinct-2021-complete-studio-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134744/RMB-Instinct-2021-complete-studio-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134744/RMB-Instinct-2021-complete-studio-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134744/RMB-Instinct-2021-complete-studio-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>The new Instinct offers 140mm of rear travel, and all models come with 150mm forks. Complete bikes are available with Smoothwall carbon or FORM Alloy frames. The Instinct now looks similar to the new Altitudes, with an updated tubing profile that provides increased front end stiffness.</p><p>The Instinct features dual bearings in the chainstay/seatstay junction, shielded bearings in all pivot points, and the carbon frames use a modular bolt-on shock mount. Both wheel sizes can fit tires up to 2.6” wide, and chainrings up to 34t.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134903/RMB-Instinct-2021-top-tube.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134903/RMB-Instinct-2021-top-tube.jpg\" alt=\"Rocky Mountain Bikes 2021 Instinct, top tube\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134903/RMB-Instinct-2021-top-tube.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134903/RMB-Instinct-2021-top-tube.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134903/RMB-Instinct-2021-top-tube-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134903/RMB-Instinct-2021-top-tube-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134903/RMB-Instinct-2021-top-tube-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134903/RMB-Instinct-2021-top-tube-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134903/RMB-Instinct-2021-top-tube-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134903/RMB-Instinct-2021-top-tube.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134903/RMB-Instinct-2021-top-tube-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134903/RMB-Instinct-2021-top-tube-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134903/RMB-Instinct-2021-top-tube-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134903/RMB-Instinct-2021-top-tube-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134903/RMB-Instinct-2021-top-tube-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Carbon Instinct frames feature fully guided internal cable routing, while the alloy frames utilize large ports for easy cable access. Both can host North American or moto brake setups, and keep the cables from rattling.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134730/RMB-Instinct-2021-chain-guard.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134730/RMB-Instinct-2021-chain-guard.jpg\" alt=\"Rocky Mountain Bikes 2021 Instinct, chain guard\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134730/RMB-Instinct-2021-chain-guard.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134730/RMB-Instinct-2021-chain-guard.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134730/RMB-Instinct-2021-chain-guard-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134730/RMB-Instinct-2021-chain-guard-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134730/RMB-Instinct-2021-chain-guard-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134730/RMB-Instinct-2021-chain-guard-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134730/RMB-Instinct-2021-chain-guard-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134730/RMB-Instinct-2021-chain-guard.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134730/RMB-Instinct-2021-chain-guard-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134730/RMB-Instinct-2021-chain-guard-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134730/RMB-Instinct-2021-chain-guard-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134730/RMB-Instinct-2021-chain-guard-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134730/RMB-Instinct-2021-chain-guard-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>The Instincts come with OneUp Components’ V2 chain guides, held up by RMB’s new Canadarm mount. The frames also include a full-length downtube protector, a noise-cancelling chainstay guard, and Rocky’s Canadian Shield mudguard behind the BB.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134846/RMB-Instinct-2021-suspension-chart.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134846/RMB-Instinct-2021-suspension-chart.jpg\" alt=\"Rocky Mountain Bikes 2021 Instinct, suspension chart\" width=\"786\" height=\"503\" sizes=\"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134846/RMB-Instinct-2021-suspension-chart.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134846/RMB-Instinct-2021-suspension-chart.jpg 786w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134846/RMB-Instinct-2021-suspension-chart-297x190.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134846/RMB-Instinct-2021-suspension-chart-120x77.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134846/RMB-Instinct-2021-suspension-chart-768x491.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134846/RMB-Instinct-2021-suspension-chart-696x445.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134846/RMB-Instinct-2021-suspension-chart-656x420.jpg 656w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134846/RMB-Instinct-2021-suspension-chart.jpg 786w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134846/RMB-Instinct-2021-suspension-chart-297x190.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134846/RMB-Instinct-2021-suspension-chart-120x77.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134846/RMB-Instinct-2021-suspension-chart-768x491.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134846/RMB-Instinct-2021-suspension-chart-696x445.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134846/RMB-Instinct-2021-suspension-chart-656x420.jpg 656w\"></a></p><p>While it shares many design features with the new Altitudes, the Instinct gets its own unique suspension tune. The Altitude is designed for aggressive trail riding and enduro racing, whereas the Instinct was built to pedal all day long.</p><p>Generally speaking RMB’s suspension curve aims to provide a soft initial stroke, supportive mid-stroke and progressive end-stroke. The bikes also include size-specific suspension tunes including smaller 190 x 45mm rear shocks for the two smallest sizes to allow for a smaller frame and lighter suspension kinematic. Medium through XL frames get a 210 x 52.5mm rear shock, while all frames run 140mm of rear travel.</p><h3>Wheel size split:</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134809/RMB-Instinct-2021-frame-profiles.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134809/RMB-Instinct-2021-frame-profiles.jpg\" alt=\"Rocky Mountain Bikes 2021 Instinct, frame standover graphic\" width=\"725\" height=\"304\" sizes=\"(max-width: 725px) 100vw, 725px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134809/RMB-Instinct-2021-frame-profiles.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134809/RMB-Instinct-2021-frame-profiles.jpg 725w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134809/RMB-Instinct-2021-frame-profiles-297x125.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134809/RMB-Instinct-2021-frame-profiles-120x50.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134809/RMB-Instinct-2021-frame-profiles-696x292.jpg 696w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134809/RMB-Instinct-2021-frame-profiles.jpg 725w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134809/RMB-Instinct-2021-frame-profiles-297x125.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134809/RMB-Instinct-2021-frame-profiles-120x50.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134809/RMB-Instinct-2021-frame-profiles-696x292.jpg 696w\"></a></p><p>RMB has set up the Instinct with different wheel sizes on different sized frames. The XS Instinct will come on 27.5” wheels only, but the Small frame will offer riders their choice of 27.5” or 29”. Medium, Large and XL frames roll on 29’s only.</p><p>To accommodate shorter riders, the XS and Small Instinct frames offer a different shape with a lowered top tube and reduced standover height. RMB also offers size-specific suspension tunes on their bikes so whether you’re buying an XS or an XL, you shouldn’t have to go to extremes to get the suspension set up properly.</p><h3>10mm dropout flip-chip:</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134752/RMB-Instinct-2021-dropout-flip-chip.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134752/RMB-Instinct-2021-dropout-flip-chip.jpg\" alt=\"Rocky Mountain Bikes 2021 Instinct, dropout flip chip\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134752/RMB-Instinct-2021-dropout-flip-chip.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134752/RMB-Instinct-2021-dropout-flip-chip.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134752/RMB-Instinct-2021-dropout-flip-chip-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134752/RMB-Instinct-2021-dropout-flip-chip-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134752/RMB-Instinct-2021-dropout-flip-chip-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134752/RMB-Instinct-2021-dropout-flip-chip-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134752/RMB-Instinct-2021-dropout-flip-chip-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134752/RMB-Instinct-2021-dropout-flip-chip.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134752/RMB-Instinct-2021-dropout-flip-chip-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134752/RMB-Instinct-2021-dropout-flip-chip-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134752/RMB-Instinct-2021-dropout-flip-chip-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134752/RMB-Instinct-2021-dropout-flip-chip-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134752/RMB-Instinct-2021-dropout-flip-chip-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Another feature of RMB’s updated frame platform is a 10mm chainstay length adjustment. A flip-chip in the rear dropout allows you the choice of riding in Short or Long mode, opting for more agility or better stability. RMB supplies their own flippable brake mount (which fits a 180mm rear rotor) and in Long mode the frame is compatible with SRAM’s UDH universal derailleur hangers.</p><h3>Ride 9 chip:</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134839/RMB-Instinct-2021-ride-9-chip.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134839/RMB-Instinct-2021-ride-9-chip.jpg\" alt=\"Rocky Mountain Bikes 2021 Instinct, Ride 9 chip\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134839/RMB-Instinct-2021-ride-9-chip.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134839/RMB-Instinct-2021-ride-9-chip.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134839/RMB-Instinct-2021-ride-9-chip-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134839/RMB-Instinct-2021-ride-9-chip-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134839/RMB-Instinct-2021-ride-9-chip-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134839/RMB-Instinct-2021-ride-9-chip-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134839/RMB-Instinct-2021-ride-9-chip-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134839/RMB-Instinct-2021-ride-9-chip.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134839/RMB-Instinct-2021-ride-9-chip-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134839/RMB-Instinct-2021-ride-9-chip-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134839/RMB-Instinct-2021-ride-9-chip-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134839/RMB-Instinct-2021-ride-9-chip-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134839/RMB-Instinct-2021-ride-9-chip-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>The new Instinct features Rocky Mountain’s Ride 9 chip, which adjusts the frame geometry and shock rate. Head and seat tube angles don’t change by much across the chip’s nine positions, but the frame’s reach ranges by 12mm’s and stack height varies by 9-10mm. Chainstay length and bottom bracket height are not affected by the Ride 9 chip.</p><p>Shock rate is noticeably affected as you move the Ride 9 chip from one end to the other. The steeper the bike gets the more linear the shock feels, and as you go slacker the shock’s progressivity ramps up. Adjusting the chip is pretty simple, you just have to look up which setting is which!</p><h3>Geometry:</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134831/RMB-Instinct-2021-geometry-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134831/RMB-Instinct-2021-geometry-2.jpg\" alt=\"Rocky Mountain Bikes 2021 Instinct, geo chart\" width=\"722\" height=\"887\" sizes=\"(max-width: 722px) 100vw, 722px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134831/RMB-Instinct-2021-geometry-2.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134831/RMB-Instinct-2021-geometry-2.jpg 722w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134831/RMB-Instinct-2021-geometry-2-244x300.jpg 244w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134831/RMB-Instinct-2021-geometry-2-98x120.jpg 98w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134831/RMB-Instinct-2021-geometry-2-696x855.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134831/RMB-Instinct-2021-geometry-2-342x420.jpg 342w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134831/RMB-Instinct-2021-geometry-2.jpg 722w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134831/RMB-Instinct-2021-geometry-2-244x300.jpg 244w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134831/RMB-Instinct-2021-geometry-2-98x120.jpg 98w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134831/RMB-Instinct-2021-geometry-2-696x855.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134831/RMB-Instinct-2021-geometry-2-342x420.jpg 342w\"></a></p><p>Check the above chart for all the particulars, but here are a few notes on the Instinct’s updated geometry: The new frames offer generous reach numbers, ranging between 456-468mm for a Medium and 481-493mm for a Large. Head tube angles range from 65° to 66.6°, while the seat masts are all between 76-77.6°.</p><p>Out back, chainstay lengths for 29ers are the same across all sizes, and can be as short as 436mm and grow up to 449mm depending on the dropout position and Ride 9 chip. The 27.5” frames rear ends range from 425-439mm.</p><h3>2021 Instinct model lineup:</h3><p>Rocky Mountain is offering the new Instinct in six carbon builds (plus a carbon frame kit) and two aluminum models. All models are available now, and since there are so many check out RMB’s website for build specs on each. Frame color options for all models are Ice Ice baby/UD Carbon/Black Dog or Violet Hills/Enter Sandman/Black Dog (with framesets only available in the latter).</p><figure id=\"attachment_252664\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-252664\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134716/RMB-Instinct-2021-Carbon-99-side.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134716/RMB-Instinct-2021-Carbon-99-side.jpg\" alt=\"Rocky Mountain Bikes 2021 Instinct, Carbon 99, side\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134716/RMB-Instinct-2021-Carbon-99-side.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134716/RMB-Instinct-2021-Carbon-99-side.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134716/RMB-Instinct-2021-Carbon-99-side-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134716/RMB-Instinct-2021-Carbon-99-side-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134716/RMB-Instinct-2021-Carbon-99-side-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134716/RMB-Instinct-2021-Carbon-99-side-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134716/RMB-Instinct-2021-Carbon-99-side-747x420.jpg 747w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134716/RMB-Instinct-2021-Carbon-99-side.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134716/RMB-Instinct-2021-Carbon-99-side-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134716/RMB-Instinct-2021-Carbon-99-side-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134716/RMB-Instinct-2021-Carbon-99-side-768x432.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134716/RMB-Instinct-2021-Carbon-99-side-696x392.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134716/RMB-Instinct-2021-Carbon-99-side-747x420.jpg 747w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-252664\">2021 Instinct Carbon 99</figcaption></figure><p>Instinct Carbon 99: $10,449</p><p>Instinct Carbon 90: $9,399</p><p>Instinct Carbon 70 Coil: $7,629</p><p>Instinct Carbon 70: $6,899</p><p>Instinct Carbon 50: $5,549</p><p>Instinct Carbon 30: $4,499</p><figure id=\"attachment_252663\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-252663\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134704/RMB-Instinct-2021-alloy-50-side.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08134704/RMB-Instinct-2021